<font color="#FF0000">SO THERE, TOMMY TWO SHOES</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov  6 22:59:45 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Oh yeah!  Well Mom's got plenty of fire and guts.. so who cares if she has bad taste?<br><br>
I'm gonna write her a poem...Mr. Goodie Two Shoes(gravel kicker..grunt..hillbilly..pumpkin roller..half pizza breath!)<br><br>
&quot;MOM WAITS&quot;<br><br>
BY Mustang Two Four (her new favorite)<br><br>
In her tattered robe, she sits by the window,<br>
bathed by the light of the moon.<br>
Scarcely breathing, she watches the road,<br>
hoping that he'll appear there soon.<br><br>
But, the silvery lane is cold and empty,<br>
except for the fallen leaves.<br>
Nothing moves but the gingham curtains, <br>
that sway in the chilling breeze.<br><br>
Her heart is sad and heavy<br>
but her fears are all denied.<br>
She refuses to accept the foolish thought,<br>
&quot;that her son has really died.&quot;<br><br>
&quot;He's missing in action,&quot; the message stated,<br>
and she remembers that tragic report.<br>
Yet, her hope won't die, unless she dies,<br>
and that is her last resort.<br><br>
Then, briefly, her son appears on the trace,<br>
marching along and whistling a tune.<br>
Desperately, she calls to her long lost boy,<br>
But, he ambles away by the light of the moon.<br><br>
from &quot;Scars and Stripes, Forever&quot; copywrite 1990 E. Ramon
